<br>
Any information would be appreciated, since I haven't grouped much because of the language barrier, hard to fight as a group when no one understands a word your saying.<br>
<br>
Sekhmal Khan<br>
Beastlord of the Vah Shir <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usnoutfv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Snout FV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 65<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/26/02 4:53:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1451.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Training Language's Question</span><hr size=1> Yes, Common = Human speak. All humans, including Barbarians and Erudites, speak Human.<br>
<br>
From what I've heard that Dark Elvish is the &quot;common&quot; of the evil races. <br>
<br>
From my personal experience, Human seems to be the &quot;common&quot; language for commerce. <br>
<br>
Anyhow, just my observations.<br>
<br>
